"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432676","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The 2010 Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR) announced the cancellation of the Nimrod MRA4 which was 11 years late and nearly £800 million over budget. It acknowledged what would result in a capability gap that would be mitigated by using a combination of other surveillance aircraft, including those from Allies, as well as ships and submarines. SDSR 2015 announced we will buy nine new Maritime Patrol Aircraft.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:32:24.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432676/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432676/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432676/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what military assets his Department propose to use to undertake maritime patrol functions between the Boeing P8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft comes into service.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432677","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>As with any acquisition programme, the Boeing P-8A - along with a number of other potential platforms - was assessed against the system's ability to meet the Department's Key User Requirements, using a combination of scientific, technical and operational analysis, as well as industry's ability to deliver the programme in a timely and cost-effective manner, to meet the capability need within budget.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:25:01.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432677/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432677/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432677/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what criteria his Department used to procure the Boeing P8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft fleet.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432678","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The UK is in negotiations with Boeing on the route to contract for P-8, which will determine how the programme will affect UK-based jobs. It is expected the P-8 will have a significant impact on the UK economy: P-8 is based on the Boeing 737, the supply chain for which already includes UK industry, and the UK also manufactures subsystems of the P-8. Purchase of the aircraft will also create opportunities for UK industry to bid for training and support contracts, and basing of this fleet at RAF Lossiemouth will bring significant economic benefits to Scotland. Boeing estimates that in total, its entire P-8 programme could generate over US$1 billion to the UK supply chain and economy.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:42:41.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432678/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432678/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432678/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the number of UK-based jobs in each region likely to be sustained by his Department's decision to procure the Boeing P8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft fleet.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432679","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The P-8A uses the 'boom and receptacle' method of in-flight refuelling. As such, the P-8A will not be able to refuel from RAF Voyager Aircraft, which use a different configuration for air-to-air refuelling.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:23:54.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432679/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432679/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Boeing P8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft will be capable of being refuelled by RAF Voyagers aircraft.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432680","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Apache Capability Sustainment Programme is currently in the Assessment Phase and the investment decision is anticipated in summer 2016 to enable orderly upgrade of our existing fleet as they reach their out-of-service date.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17844 ; 17845","2015-12-03T16:20:28.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432680/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432680/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Apache AH-64 Helicopter","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 31 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, when he plans for the Apache helicopter upgrade to take place.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432681","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Apache Capability Sustainment Programme is currently in the Assessment Phase and the investment decision is anticipated in summer 2016 to enable orderly upgrade of our existing fleet as they reach their out-of-service date.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17843 ; 17845","2015-12-03T16:20:28.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432681/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432681/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Apache AH-64 Helicopter","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 31 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what estimate his Department has made of the cost of the Apache helicopter upgrade.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432682","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Apache Capability Sustainment Programme is currently in the Assessment Phase and the investment decision is anticipated in summer 2016 to enable orderly upgrade of our existing fleet as they reach their out-of-service date.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17843 ; 17844","2015-12-03T16:20:28.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432682/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432682/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432682/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Apache AH-64 Helicopter","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 31 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what estimate he has made of the number of jobs likely to be sustained by the Apache helicopter upgrade.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432683","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>In the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 (Cm9161) we have increased our ambition so that for Joint Force 2025 we will be able to deploy an expeditionary force of around 50,000 including greater contributions from the air and maritime domain. This is is the largest scale operation that Defence plans to be able to deliver whilst continuing to conduct a range of concurrent &quot;fixed&quot; tasks such as defending the homeland, running military bases and training our military personnel. The scale and nature of the deployment means that there is no specific force generation ratio associated with it.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-03T16:22:31.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432683/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432683/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432683/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what he plans the force generation ratios to be for the expeditionary force of 50,000 personnel announced in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432684","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<p>Of the 10,000 military personnel on standby in the UK, some units are placed on standby on a rolling basis, while others have specific geographic responsibilities which they meet from their available manpower.</p><p>Military personnel will be drawn from all three Services, with the majority being supplied from the Army.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","17848","2015-12-04T14:32:26.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432684/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432684/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432684/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, from which branches of the armed forces the 10,000 military personnel on standby to assist civil authorities in case of significant terrorist incidents referred to in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 are to be drawn.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432685","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<p>Of the 10,000 military personnel on standby in the UK, some units are placed on standby on a rolling basis, while others have specific geographic responsibilities which they meet from their available manpower.</p><p>Military personnel will be drawn from all three Services, with the majority being supplied from the Army.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","17847","2015-12-04T14:32:26.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432685/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432685/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432685/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what he plans the force generation ratios to be for the 10,000 military personnel on standby to assist civil authorities in case of significant terrorist incidents referred to in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432686","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-01","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 16 November 2015 to Question 15341 to the hon. Member for Stretford and Urmston (Kate Green).</p><p>http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-11-06/15341/</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-01T16:34:33.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432686/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432686/answer","20151116_15341_MOD_Families.docx","20151116_15341_MOD_Families.docx","15341 - QnA extract on MOD Families","15341 - QnA extract on MOD Families","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432686/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Ministry of Defence: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what training his Department has provided to staff on the family test; what other steps he has taken to raise awareness of the family test among staff of his Department; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Ansell","Eastbourne","Caroline Ansell","17923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432687","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>Spending Review 15 and the Strategic Defence and Security Review confirmed that the number of Ministry of Defence (MOD) civilians would reduce by almost 30% to 41,000 by the end of this Parliament. The majority of these reductions will be generated from pre-existing and emerging change programmes. The remaining reductions are estimated to produce a saving of £300million over the next five years which will be used to reinvest within the Defence Programme. The MOD will undertake a number of studies to determine how best to generate this saving without impacting front-line outputs.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-02T16:12:13.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432687/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432687/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432687/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 33 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, how much his Department plans to save by reducing the civil service headcount in his Department to 41,000.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432688","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-01","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave her on 30 November 2015 to Questions 17752, 17733 and 17735.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","17916","2015-12-01T16:35:08.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432688/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432688/answer","20151130_17752_MOD_Staff.docx","20151130_17752_MOD_Staff.docx","17752 - QnA extract on MOD Staff","17752 - QnA extract on MOD Staff","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432688/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 33 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, how many posts he plans to lose in each section of his Department.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432689","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-01","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave her on 30 November 2015 to Questions 17752, 17733 and 17735.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","17915","2015-12-01T16:35:08.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432689/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432689/answer","20151130_17752_MOD_Staff.docx","20151130_17752_MOD_Staff.docx","17752 - QnA extract on MOD Staff","17752 - QnA extract on MOD Staff","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432689/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 33 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what his timetable is for reducing his Department's civil service headcount.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432690","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>As stated in the Spending Review 2015 the Ministry of Defence expects to dispose of sites generating £1 billion of receipts in the financial years 2016-17 to 2020-21.</p><p>The Department does not disclose annual breakdowns due to the potential for prejudice to its commercial interests.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-02T16:19:54.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432690/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432690/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432690/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Ministry of Defence: Land","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of his Department's receipts from land sales in each year until 2020.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432691","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>In the current financial year, 2015-16, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) expects to sell the Old War Office Building, Islington TA Centre, a part of Shorncliffe Garrison, Canterbury TA Centre and around 70 smaller sites throughout the UK which are mainly small parts of larger establishments.</p><p>The MOD is committed to reducing the size of its estate holding to the most appropriate size and lay down required for our Armed Forces. As set out in Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 the Department intends to reduce the built estate by 30% with the aim of providing a smaller more sustainable estate in support of Military capabilities.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-02T17:13:57.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432691/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432691/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432691/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Ministry of Defence: Land","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which sites owned by his Department he plans to sell in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432692","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>The Footprint Strategy examines the Defence Estate across the UK, with the aim of providing a smaller more sustainable estate in support of Military capabilities. Current work to define the Defence Footprint Strategy, will contribute to the Governments commitment to release public sector land for house building in this Parliament.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-02T16:12:55.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432692/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432692/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432692/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which bases he plans to close as a result of the outcome of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432693","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" rowspan="5"></td><td colspan="6" rowspan="5"><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 1 December 2015 to Question 17447 to the hon. Member for Glasgow South West (Chris Stephens).</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17876","2015-12-03T16:42:14.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432693/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432693/answer","Hansard  Extract  17447 1 December 2015.docx","Hansard  Extract  17447 1 December 2015.docx","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432693/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Warships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 30 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what estimate he has made of the cost of each of the new logistic ships.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432694","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Type 26 Global Combat Ship, designed to provide an anti-submarine warfare capability, will be a multi-mission warship designed for joint and multinational operations across the full spectrum of warfare, including complex combat operations, counter piracy, humanitarian and disaster relief work.</p><p>It will be capable of operating independently for significant periods, or as part of a task group. Its design is inherently flexible, allowing greater choice in operational tasking through the incorporation of modular systems, to allow incremental upgrades to its systems through the life-time of the class. These include the flexible strike silo (able to host anti-submarine, anti-ship and, if required, land attack strike missiles) and the modular mission bay (able to host unmanned air, surface or sub-surface systems, boats for an embarked force, further command facilities or humanitarian relief stores).</p><p>I am withholding further detail as its disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:33:49.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432694/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432694/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432694/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the operational capabilities are of the Type 26 frigates announced in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432695","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The cost and schedule of the general purpose frigate programme outlined in the White Paper National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence And Security Review 2015 (Cmd 9161) has yet to be determined. The programme will be scoped during a concept study as part of the programme announced by the Prime Minister on 23 November 2015 (Official Report: column 1049).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17856","2015-12-03T16:41:03.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432695/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432695/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432695/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 31 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, when he plans for the new class of general purpose frigates to be in service.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432696","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review (Cm9161) endorsed the requirement for eight of the anti-submarine warfare variant of the Type 26 Global Combat Ship to replace the eight Type 23 frigates that currently fulfil this role. The review also concluded that the remainder of the Navy's future frigate requirement would be better met by a new class of lighter, flexible, general purpose frigates than by the five general purpose Type 26 ships previously planned. This new class of frigate will be procured in greater numbers enabling an increase in the size of the Navy's destroyer and frigate fleet above the 19 ships currently in service. This will further improve the Royal Navy's ability to deliver the full range of defence, warfighting and maritime security tasks well into the middle of the 21st Century.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:36:06.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432696/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432696/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432696/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the strategic rationale is for the change in the total number of Type 26 frigates to be built.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432697","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" rowspan="5"></td><td colspan="6" rowspan="5"><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 1 December 2015 to Question 17447 to the hon. Member for Glasgow South West (Chris Stephens).</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17877","2015-12-03T16:42:14.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432697/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432697/answer","Hansard  Extract  17447 1 December 2015.docx","Hansard  Extract  17447 1 December 2015.docx","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432697/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Warships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 30 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, when he plans for three new logistic ships to come into service.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432698","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>On current planning assumptions, the new military personnel numbers provided for in the Strategic Defence and Security Review will begin to come into effect in 2016 and will be achieved by 2022 for the Royal Navy and 2018 for the Royal Air Force.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-03T16:31:27.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432698/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432698/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432698/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans for the increase in (a) Royal Navy and (b) Royal Air Force personnel provided for in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 to take place.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432699","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The number of general purpose frigates to be procured through the programme has yet to be determined. Work on the programme will be scoped initially during the concept study outlined in the White Paper National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 (Cmd 9161).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:34:28.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432699/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432699/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432699/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 31 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what his Department's planning assumptions are for the number of vessels of the new class of general purpose frigates which his Department plans to procure.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432700","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The cost and schedule of the general purpose frigate programme outlined in the White Paper National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence And Security Review 2015 (Cmd 9161) has yet to be determined. The programme will be scoped during a concept study as part of the programme announced by the Prime Minister on 23 November 2015 (Official Report: column 1049).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17880","2015-12-03T16:41:03.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432700/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432700/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432700/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 31 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what estimate he has made of the cost of the new general purpose frigates.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432701","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>As explained in the White Paper National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 (Cmd 9161) we intend to maintain a fleet of 19 frigates and destroyers until the 2030s when the introduction of a new class of general purpose frigate will allow this size of the fleet to increase. The timetable for the general purpose frigate programme, and the number of ships we intend to buy, have yet to be determined and will be shaped by the Shipbuilding Strategy we will publish in 2016.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:40:09.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432701/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432701/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432701/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what planning assumptions he has made of the Royal Navy's frigate fleet size in each year from 2015 to 2040.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432702","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Three River Class Patrol Vessels are already under construction, the first two of which are scheduled to enter service in 2018 and the third in 2019. The contract for two further vessels, and therefore their delivery schedule, has yet to be agreed and will be influenced by the Shipbuilding Strategy to be published in 2016.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:35:38.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432702/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432702/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432702/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Patrol Craft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 31 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, when he plans for the off-shore patrol vessels being procured by his Department to come into service.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432703","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<br /><p>As with the three Offshore Patrol Vessels (OPVs) currently under construction, the two additional OPVs referred to in the White Paper National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence And Security Review 2015 (Cmd 9161) will be built at BAE Systems' (BAES) shipyards on the Clyde. Decisions about the appointment of sub-contractors to the supply chain will be a matter for BAES.</p><br /><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:43:47.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432703/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432703/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432703/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Patrol Craft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 31 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, whether he plans for the off-shore patrol vessels being procured by his Department to be manufactured using the same supply chain as the off-shore patrol vessels under construction.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432704","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<br /><p>When HMS OCEAN entered service in 1998 she had a specified service life, based on her build specification, of 20 years.</p><p>The decision to retire HMS Ocean is consistent with the intent expressed in paragraph 2.A.5 in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2010. As part of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 the Royal Navy will retain two landing Platform Dock vessels in the fleet.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-04T14:17:57.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432704/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432704/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432704/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons it is proposed to retire HMS Ocean in 2018; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432705","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review included a commitment to invest further in Typhoon's capabilities, including ground attack. Under current plans, the in-service dates on Typhoon will be August 2018 for Storm Shadow and December 2018 for Brimstone.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-30T17:17:35.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432705/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432705/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432705/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Guided Weapons: European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, by when he plans for Stormshadow and Brimstone missile systems to be integrated with Typhoon aircraft.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432706","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Over the next five years, the Department plans to spend around £6.5 billion on the procurement, support and testing of sophisticated weapons systems.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:21:52.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432706/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432706/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432706/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Weapons: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department plans to spend on new precision weapons systems in each year from 2015 to 2020.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432707","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Under plans announced in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 (Cm9161), Sentinel will be extended in service into the next decade.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:21:18.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432707/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432707/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432707/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Sentinel Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to retire the Sentinel aircraft from service.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432708","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review announced the extended life of the Sentinel into the next decade. Detailed cost estimates are currently being finalised.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:24:29.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432708/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432708/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432708/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Sentinel Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of his Department's (a) running and (b) maintenance costs for Sentinel aircraft in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432709","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>It is estimated that the running costs for the Command Support Air Transport Fleet would be some £19 million - £20 million per annum, in each year from 2015-2020.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:23:22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432709/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432709/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432709/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of his Department's running costs for the Command Support Air Transport fleet in each year from 2015 to 2020.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432710","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<br /><p>The Air Command running costs, in £millions and by financial year, for the Command Support Air Transport fleet based at RAF Northolt are as follows:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p><br></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>14.8</p></td><td><p>15.9</p></td><td><p>18.8</p></td><td><p>19.1</p></td><td><p>18.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Costs for the current financial year 2015-16, have not yet been finalised.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:18:36.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432710/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432710/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432710/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on running costs for the Command Support Air Transport fleet in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432711","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>A full assessment phase will be undertaken to ensure that any recapitalisation decisions provide the most efficient way of delivering capability and offer best value for money.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:43:14.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432711/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432711/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432711/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the cost of recapitalising the Command Support Air Transport fleet.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432712","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>As stated in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 15 (Cm9161), our latest estimate of the total cost to manufacture the four Successor submarines is £31 billion; we will also set a contingency of £10 billion. This level of contingency represents about 35% of the costs to completion and is a prudent estimate based on past experience of large, complex projects.</p><p>We expect that, once the Successor submarines come into service, the in-service costs of the UK's nuclear deterrent, which include the costs of the Atomic Weapons Establishment, will be similar to those of today - around 6% of the Defence budget.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:39:02.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432712/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432712/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432712/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Nuclear Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 36 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what the costs are of the Successor programme.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432713","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Expenditure from the centralised Ministry of Defence Science and Technology Programme under the Department's Chief Scientific Adviser for each year since 2010 (inclusive of non-recoverable VAT at current prices) is given below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Defence Science and Technology programme expenditure (£million)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>422</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>432</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>444</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>435</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>436</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:38:06.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432713/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432713/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432713/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Ministry of Defence: Science","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much of his Department's budget has been spent on science and technology in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432714","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Work is under way to examine the options. We will announce further details in due course.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-03T16:25:28.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432714/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432714/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his timetable is for introducing proposals to amend the legal standing on which the armed forces undertake operations, as set out in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432715","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>This information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost. The Ministry of Defence (MOD) funds Armed Forces charities through grants in aid, grants, normal commercial contract arrangements, and (since 2013) through fines levied on banks for the attempted manipulation of Libor (the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015 has detailed the charities receiving Libor funding over the next three years). The regional distribution of MOD funding is a matter for the recipient charities.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-02T16:17:21.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432715/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432715/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432715/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces: Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much money his Department gave to support armed forces charities in each region in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432716","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<p>The decision as to where locations of where British Defence Staffs (BDS) will be based has yet to be finalised. The intention of establishing BDS is to build on our existing overseas networks (including Defence Attaches, Liaison and Exchange Officers and Training Teams) in order to provide a cross-regional focus, and improved coordination and coherence, to Defence Engagement activity. We review our overseas footprint regularly to match the requirement and this work is in conjunction with the development of a Defence Engagement Career Field within the UK Armed Forces, improved training, preparation and development for our overseas cohort and greater alignment with other Government Departments with deployed networks.</p><p>Once decisions have been made on the future of BDS I will write to the hon. Member to update her.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-12-04T14:08:24.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432716/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432716/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432716/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 49 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, in which countries he plans to locate British defence staffs in 2016.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432717","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>The Department is currently working to identify the implications of the Spending Review settlement for specific elements of the Defence budget, and has not yet confirmed the funding which will be allocated to Defence Engagement activities.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-12-02T16:19:10.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432717/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432717/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much he plans to spend on defence engagement functions in each year from 2015 to 2020.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432718","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Up to £300 million will be spread across Front Line Commands and a number of capabilities. It will not only be invested to enhance operational communications, but also to renew the existing air defence system and upgrade infrastructure, all in the context of the Falkland Islands.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:22:05.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432718/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432718/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432718/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Ministry of Defence: Communication","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 25 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what projects he plans to fund from the £300 million investment in operational communications.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17948"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432719","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Each year since 2010 the Royal Navy Gibraltar Squadron (RNGS) has consisted of two SCIMITAR Class Patrol Boats, HMS SCIMITAR and HMS SABRE and three Rigid Hull Inflatable Boats (RHIBs). It is also frequently bolstered by Royal Navy vessels transiting the region.</p><br /><p>Since 2010 there have been 22 stationed personnel which were increased by five temporary augmentees following a pattern of increased Spanish incursions in 2012. After a review in 2014 the number of personnel was permanently uplifted to 26.</p><br /><p>The following table represents the financial expenditure incurred by British Forces Gibraltar in support of the RNGS in each year since 2010.</p><p>Figures are in millions.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p><br></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1.3</p></td><td><p>1.4</p></td><td><p>1.4</p></td><td><p>1.3</p></td><td><p>1.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","17950","2015-12-03T16:28:25.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432719/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432719/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432719/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Gibraltar: Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the size of the Royal Navy Gibraltar Squadron has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17949"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432720","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Each year since 2010 the Royal Navy Gibraltar Squadron (RNGS) has consisted of two SCIMITAR Class Patrol Boats, HMS SCIMITAR and HMS SABRE and three Rigid Hull Inflatable Boats (RHIBs). It is also frequently bolstered by Royal Navy vessels transiting the region.</p><br /><p>Since 2010 there have been 22 stationed personnel which were increased by five temporary augmentees following a pattern of increased Spanish incursions in 2012. After a review in 2014 the number of personnel was permanently uplifted to 26.</p><br /><p>The following table represents the financial expenditure incurred by British Forces Gibraltar in support of the RNGS in each year since 2010.</p><p>Figures are in millions.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p><br></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1.3</p></td><td><p>1.4</p></td><td><p>1.4</p></td><td><p>1.3</p></td><td><p>1.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","17949","2015-12-03T16:28:26.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432720/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432720/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432720/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Gibraltar: Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on the Royal Navy Gibraltar Squadron in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432721","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>It has been agreed with Her Majesty's Treasury that the Ministry of Defence will be able to draw down £2.1 billion from the Joint Security Fund over the remainder of this Parliament.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-12-02T16:15:23.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432721/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432721/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432721/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer on the Joint Security Fund; and how much his Department may draw from that fund in each year from 2015 to 2020.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432722","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Designing and building submarines is one of the largest programmes and one of the most complex activities that the Ministry of Defence and UK Industry has ever undertaken. It is the purpose of a design phase to improve our understanding of costs and timescales, which we have now done. The current estimates reflect what we have learned since the design phase began.</p><p>As stated in the Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR) 2015 (Cm9161), our latest estimate of the total cost to manufacture the four Successor submarines reflects greater maturity of the design and understanding of the supply chain, amounts to £31 billion; we will also set a contingency of £10 billion. This level of contingency represents about 35% of the costs to completion and is a prudent estimate based on past experience of large, complex projects.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17736 ; 17739 ; 17897","2015-12-03T16:21:00.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432722/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432722/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432722/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Nuclear Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons the cost estimates of the Successor class of submarines in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 differs from his Department's previous cost estimates for those submarines.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432723","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<p>As stated in paragraph 4.76 in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 15 (Cm9161), we expect the first Successor submarine to enter service in the early 2030s.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-04T14:10:46.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432723/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432723/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432723/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans for the first of the Successor submarines to enter service; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432724","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-04","<p>As announced in the Chancellor's speech of 17 November, a new National Cyber Security Strategy will be launched in 2016, implemented through a new National Cyber Security Programme. The new programme will determine how much of the £1.9 billion investment is spent each financial year to March 2021.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-04T12:58:43.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432724/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432724/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432724/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Electronic Warfare: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to paragraph 4.105 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, how much of the £1.9 billion investment in cyber defence he plans to spend in each year until 2020.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17953"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432725","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Designing and building submarines is one of the largest programmes and one of the most complex activities that the Ministry of Defence and UK Industry has ever undertaken. It is the purpose of a design phase to improve our understanding of costs and timescales, which we have now done. The current estimates reflect what we have learned since the design phase began.</p><p>As stated in the Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR) 2015 (Cm9161), our latest estimate of the total cost to manufacture the four Successor submarines reflects greater maturity of the design and understanding of the supply chain, amounts to £31 billion; we will also set a contingency of £10 billion. This level of contingency represents about 35% of the costs to completion and is a prudent estimate based on past experience of large, complex projects.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17736 ; 17739 ; 17895","2015-12-03T16:21:00.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432725/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432725/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432725/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Nuclear Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons the proposed in-service date for the Successor class of submarines has been postponed.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432726","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-04","<p>A new 5 year National Cyber Security Programme will commence in April 2016. Details of the programme will be published next year.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-04T12:57:49.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432726/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432726/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432726/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Electronic Warfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what his plans are for the 2015-2020 National Cyber Security Programme; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432727","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-04","<p>As announced in the Chancellor's speech of 17 November, a National Cyber Centre will be launched in 2016. Work is underway to determine the exact costs, as part of the £1.9bn budget for cyber security announce in the Spending Review.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-04T12:56:11.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432727/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432727/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432727/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Electronic Warfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the cost of establishing a National Cyber Security Centre.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432728","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-04","<p>As announced in the Chancellor's speech of 17 November, a National Cyber Centre will be launched in 2016. The new National Cyber Security programme will determine which cyber capabilities will be incorporated in the National Cyber Centre.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-04T12:57:01.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432728/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432728/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432728/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Electronic Warfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what cyber capabilities he plans to be based at the National Cyber Centre.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432729","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>We will provide further updates on Armed Forces Pay Reform in 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","17899","2015-12-03T16:26:03.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432729/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432729/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432729/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 33 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, if he will set out the elements of the new pay model for members of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432730","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>The number of International Defence Training places provided to partners at UK training establishments over the last five Financial Years (FY) is as follows:</p><p>2010-11 - 3,418</p><p>2011-12 - 3,087</p><p>2012-13 - 3,048</p><p>2013-14 - 2,674</p><p>2014-15 - 3,078</p><p>We provide International Defence Training places on a wide variety of military training courses. The allocation and take-up of places is a flexible process, driven partly by demand, and managed through arrangements particular to each course. Allocations are generally not programmed more than a year in advance. We cannot quantify in advance the total number of training places which will be offered in each year but intend to increase the training we offer to international partners. We have identified additional places on a number of specific courses including, for example, at the Defence Academy and the Royal College of Defence Studies.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","17958","2015-12-02T16:11:00.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432730/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432730/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Military Aid: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many training places have been made available for the UK's international partners in his Department's military training facilities in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432731","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>We will provide further updates on Armed Forces Pay Reform in 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","17898","2015-12-03T16:26:03.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432731/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432731/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 33 of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what estimate he has made of how many serving members in each branch of the armed forces are likely to be affected by the new pay model for members of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432732","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>The estimated saving from phasing out the commitment bonus for members of the Armed Forces is £118 million over the remainder of this Parliament and some £50 million a year thereafter.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T17:00:13.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432732/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432732/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432732/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what cost savings his Department plans to make from phasing out the commitment bonus for members of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432733","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>The number of International Defence Training places provided to partners at UK training establishments over the last five Financial Years (FY) is as follows:</p><p>2010-11 - 3,418</p><p>2011-12 - 3,087</p><p>2012-13 - 3,048</p><p>2013-14 - 2,674</p><p>2014-15 - 3,078</p><p>We provide International Defence Training places on a wide variety of military training courses. The allocation and take-up of places is a flexible process, driven partly by demand, and managed through arrangements particular to each course. Allocations are generally not programmed more than a year in advance. We cannot quantify in advance the total number of training places which will be offered in each year but intend to increase the training we offer to international partners. We have identified additional places on a number of specific courses including, for example, at the Defence Academy and the Royal College of Defence Studies.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","17957","2015-12-02T16:11:00.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432733/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432733/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432733/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Military Aid: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many training places he plans to make available for the UK's international partners in his Department's military training facilities in each year from 2016 to 2020.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432734","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-01","<p>Commitment Bonuses are being phased out over the next five years as there is insufficient evidence they significantly influence retention in the Armed Forces.</p><p>In Financial Year 2014-15 approximately 14,000 Service personnel claimed a Commitment Bonus payment. Eligibility for Commitment Bonuses ceases with effect from 1April 2021, providing eligible Other Ranks with the opportunity to claim any payments they might have already included in their financial plans.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","17903","2015-12-01T16:33:52.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432734/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432734/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432734/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of how many serving members of each branch of the armed forces are likely to be affected by the phasing out of the commitment bonus for armed forces personnel.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432735","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>There are no plans to merge or disband military units in implementing Joint Force 2025. We are committed to maintaining the size of the regular Armed Forces, not reducing the Army below 82,000, and increasing the Royal Navy and Royal Air Force by a total of 700 personnel.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-03T16:29:01.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432735/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432735/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432735/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to (a) merge and (b) disband military units in implementing Joint Force 2025.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17959"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432736","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>The amount contributed by the UK to NATO Common Funded training exercises in each year since 2010 is:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><p><strong>€ </strong><strong>million</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£ million</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p>5.197</p></td><td><p>4.480</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p>6.167</p></td><td><p>5.362</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p>5.405</p></td><td><p>4.394</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p>6.153</p></td><td><p>5.215</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p>5.093</p></td><td><p>4.107</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p>2.578</p></td><td><p>1.882</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>The figures for 2010-14 are actuals; the figures for 2015 are the current estimates.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-02T16:22:41.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432736/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432736/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432736/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","NATO: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent on contributions to NATO training exercises in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432737","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-01","<p>The savings generated by the decision to phase out commitment bonuses for the Armed Forces form part of the overall Ministry of Defence efficiency package for this Parliament.</p><p>As detailed in the Strategic Defence and Security Review (Cm 9161), efficiency savings will enable investment in a broad range of high-priority capabilities such as counter-terrorism and military surveillance to help protect the UK and our interests abroad, the procurement of a fleet of maritime patrol aircraft to increase further the protection of our nuclear deterrent and our new aircraft carriers, and funding to ensure our Armed Forces continue to be provided with the equipment they need and force protection when they are deployed.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-01T16:33:15.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432737/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432737/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432737/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how he plans to reinvest the savings achieved by phasing out the commitment bonus for members of the armed forces in the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432738","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>The estimated UK contribution to NATO Common Funded training exercises in each year from 2016 to 2020 is:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><strong>€ million</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£ million</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td><p>6.441</p></td><td><p>4.634</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td><td><p>5.939</p></td><td><p>4.272</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2018</strong></p></td><td><p>6.411</p></td><td><p>4.612</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2019</strong></p></td><td><p>5.840</p></td><td><p>4.202</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2020</strong></p></td><td><p>5.840</p></td><td><p>4.202</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>These figures are based on the latest proposed ceiling for the NATO Command Structure and Entities Programme within the 2016 NATO Resource Plan, which has yet to be finalised and is still under discussion in NATO Headquarters.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-12-02T16:24:18.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432738/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432738/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432738/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","NATO: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department plans to spend on contributions to NATO training exercises in each year from 2016 to 2020.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432739","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-01","<p>Commitment Bonuses are being phased out over the next five years as there is insufficient evidence they significantly influence retention in the Armed Forces.</p><p>In Financial Year 2014-15 approximately 14,000 Service personnel claimed a Commitment Bonus payment. Eligibility for Commitment Bonuses ceases with effect from 1April 2021, providing eligible Other Ranks with the opportunity to claim any payments they might have already included in their financial plans.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","17901","2015-12-01T16:33:52.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432739/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432739/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432739/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what timetable he has set for phasing out the commitment bonus for members of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432740","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<br /><p>Options for the composition of the new organisation will be developed and assessed for a decision in 2016. The Ministry of Defence will remain in control of the Successor submarine programme.</p><br /><p><br></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:44:26.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432740/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432740/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432740/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Nuclear Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 4.75 of the National Security and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, which (a) government departments and (b) commercial partners will be represented on the new delivery body for nuclear submarine procurement and support; and to which government department that body will report.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","17974"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432741","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 28 October 2015 to Question 13202 to the hon. Member for Gedling (Mr Coaker).</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T17:01:53.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432741/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432741/answer","20151028_13202_Commonwealth_War_Graves_Commission_Pensions.docx","20151028_13202_Commonwealth_War_Graves_Commission_Pensions.docx","13202 - QnA extraxt on CWC Pensions","13202 - QnA extraxt on CWC Pensions","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432741/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Commonwealth War Graves Commission: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions his Department has had with the Commonwealth War Graves Commission on that organisation's pension scheme; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","17964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432742","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>It is estimated that the misconduct process relating to Ministry of Defence Police officers based at the Atomic Weapons Establishment Burghfield will conclude during the first quarter of 2016. The misconduct process will conclude once all proceedings have taken place in accordance with statutory regulations.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-02T16:15:54.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432742/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432742/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432742/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Ministry of Defence Police: Disciplinary Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 9 September 2015 to Question 9672, when he expects the investigation by the Ministry of Defence Police Professional Standards Department into disciplinary matters relating to police officers based at the Atomic Weapons Establishment, Burghfield, to be completed; and for what reason that investigation has not yet been completed.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","17975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432743","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<br /><p>We expect to announce further details of the new organisation in 2016.</p><br /><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:45:00.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432743/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432743/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432743/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 4.75 of the National Security and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, by what date the new team sponsoring the defence nuclear enterprise is scheduled to be established.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","17976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432744","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The two Strike Brigades will provide a rapidly deployable agile force, with enhanced range, speed, protection and firepower, significantly enhancing the UK's ability to respond to international crises.</p><p>As previously announced on 3 September 2014 by My right hon. Friend the Defence Secretary (Michael Fallon) (Official Report, column 19WS) a contract has been awarded to deliver 589 Ajax vehicles. Detailed allocation plans have yet to be finalised. Fielding of Strike Brigades will start from 2018, delivering an initial operating capability in 2021 and moving towards Full Operating Capability from 2025.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17790","2015-12-03T16:35:12.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432744/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432744/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432744/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with how many new Scout land vehicles each of the new Strike Brigades, referred to in the National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 will be equipped.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","17930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432745","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-01","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Written Statement made by my right hon. Friend the previous Secretary of State for Defence (Philip Hammond) on 19 December 2013, (Official Report, column 124WS) on Future Reserves 2020, and the accompanying document that was placed in the Library of the House which sets out the planned growth of the trained strength of the Reserve Forces, together with the enlistment targets for the next five years.</p><p>I also refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 20 October 2015 to the hon. Member for Strangford (Mr Shannon) to Question 11812 which explained the improvements we have made to ensure we reach our target strength of 35,000 trained volunteer Reservists by 31 March 2019.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","17905 ; 17906 ; 17907 ; 17908 ; 17909","2015-12-01T16:38:02.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432745/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432745/answer","20131219_WMS_Future_Reserves_2020.docx ; 20151020_11812_Reserve_Forces_Recruitment.docx","20131219_WMS_Future_Reserves_2020.docx ; 20151020_11812_Reserve_Forces_Recruitment.docx","20131219 - WMS on Future Reserves 2020 ; 20151020 - QnA extract on Reserve Forces","20131219 - WMS on Future Reserves 2020 ; 20151020 - QnA extract on Reserve Forces","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432745/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-26","Army Reserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, by when he plans for his Department to achieve its target strength for the Army Reserve.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17904"
