r DPA</p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>General advice given to Data Controller</p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Data Controller outside UK</p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Improvement action plan agreed with Data Controller</p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>1%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br />","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-14T14:36:56.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432836/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432836/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432836/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-26","Data Protection: Assessments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much the Information Commissioner's Office has spent on processing assessments pursuant to section 42 of the Data Protection Act 1998 in each of the last five financial years; how many such requests that Office has received in each of the those years; and what the recorded outcomes were of those requests.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","17984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432837","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-03","<p>This department has liaised directly with DWP for advice and guidance on applying the Family Test in policy development. Policymakers in this department have been encouraged to attend Family test training on applying the Test and have been made aware of best practice.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-12-03T15:24:45.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432837/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432837/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-26","Ministry of Justice: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what training his Department has provided to staff on the family test; what other steps he has taken to raise awareness of the family test among staff of his Department; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Ansell","Eastbourne","Caroline Ansell","17928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432838","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-16","<p>Search engines are data controllers if they process information about living, identifiable people, for example within a search result based on a person’s name.Data controllersmust comply with the data protection principles, for example by explaining to customers how their information is collected and used. Although the main search engines are international operations, if they have an establishment in the UK, then their activities will be subject to UK data protection law.</p><p>The ICO ensures thatdata controllerscomply with the lawfor example by investigating complaints and carrying out enforcement or liaison work. The ICO will continue to engage with the search engines to ensure that the right balance is struck between online access to information and individuals’ privacy rights.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-16T16:55:22.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432838/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432838/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-26","Internet: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, (a) what obligations exist on search engine providers registered as data controllers with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) (including those with offices outside the jurisdiction) to ensure that any data processing by them complies with the Data Protection Principles and (b) what steps the ICO (i) has taken and (ii) is planning to take to ensure that such principles are complied with.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","17986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432839","Leader of the House","false","2015-12-02","<p>Spending Review 2015 set out settlements for departments and showed how the government will deliver on its priorities, eliminate the deficit, and deliver security and opportunity for working people.</p><p>Final decisions on internal departmental funding allocations for future years, including for research and development, have not yet been made.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2015-12-02T11:30:47.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432839/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432839/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2015-11-26","Leader of the House of Commons: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, how much of his Office's funding allocated in the Spending Review 2015 will be for research and development expenditure up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","17771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432840","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-12-04","<p>My Department has no funding allocated in the Spending Review 2015 for research and development expenditure. Funding for research and development expenditure in Northern Ireland is allocated to NI Executive Departments.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-12-04T14:25:59.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432840/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432840/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-11-26","Northern Ireland Office: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how much of her Department's funding allocated in the Spending Review 2015 will be for research and development expenditure up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","17772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432841","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-02","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>Following settlement of the Cabinet Office Spending Review last week, the allocation of funds to individual workstreams, including for research and development, is underway as part of the department’s business planning process to be completed in the coming months.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","17758","2015-12-02T14:39:34.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432841/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432841/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432841/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Prime Minister: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much of 10 Downing Street's funding allocated in the Spending Review 2015 will be for research and development expenditure up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","17773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432842","Prime Minister","false","2015-12-01","<p>We estimate that there are around 70,000 Syrian opposition fighters on the ground who do not belong to extremist groups, many of whom are linked to the Free Syrian Army. In addition to these 70,000, there are around 20,000 Kurdish fighters in Syria, who are also playing an important role in combating ISIL. The information we have on individual groups which forms the basis of this estimate is drawn in large part from intelligence. It would not be to the benefit of these non-extremist opposition fighters if we were to make it public to ISIL and the Syrian regime. We have very close intelligence relationships with a range of allies and partners, and share assessments with them as a matter of course.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","17826 ; 18014","2015-12-01T16:52:04.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432842/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432842/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432842/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-11-26","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, with reference to pages 18 and 19 of his response to the Foreign Affairs Select Committee's Second Report of Session 2015-16: The Extension of Offensive British Military Operation to Syria, published on 26 November 2015, what his assessment is of the capacity of the 70,000 Syrian opposition fighters referred to (a) taking territory from ISIL, (b) holding that territory and (c) administering it; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","17854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432843","Prime Minister","false","2015-12-01","<p>We estimate that there are around 70,000 Syrian opposition fighters on the ground who do not belong to extremist groups, many of whom are linked to the Free Syrian Army. In addition to these 70,000, there are around 20,000 Kurdish fighters in Syria, who are also playing an important role in combating ISIL. The information we have on individual groups which forms the basis of this estimate is drawn in large part from intelligence. It would not be to the benefit of these non-extremist opposition fighters if we were to make it public to ISIL and the Syrian regime. We have very close intelligence relationships with a range of allies and partners, and share assessments with them as a matter of course.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","17854 ; 18014","2015-12-01T16:52:04.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432843/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432843/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-11-26","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what the evidential basis is for his estimate that there are about 70,000 Syrian opposition fighters on the ground who do not belong to extremist groups; whether he has shared that estimate with all coalition partners; whether that estimate is congruent with those supplied by other partner countries in the coalition; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","17826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432844","Prime Minister","false","2015-12-01","<p>We estimate that there are around 70,000 Syrian opposition fighters on the ground who do not belong to extremist groups, many of whom are linked to the Free Syrian Army. In addition to these 70,000, there are around 20,000 Kurdish fighters in Syria, who are also playing an important role in combating ISIL. The information we have on individual groups which forms the basis of this estimate is drawn in large part from intelligence. It would not be to the benefit of these non-extremist opposition fighters if we were to make it public to ISIL and the Syrian regime. We have very close intelligence relationships with a range of allies and partners, and share assessments with them as a matter of course.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","17826 ; 17854","2015-12-01T16:52:05.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432844/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432844/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432844/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-11-26","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, with reference to oral statement of 26 November 2015, which main groups comprise the 70,000 moderate fighters in Syria he referred to in that statement; what estimate the Government has made of the number of fighters in each such group; and what the political and religious description is of each such group.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","18014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432845","Prime Minister","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Government are in regular contact with the Arab League who attended the International Syria Support Group in Vienna on 14 November. Nabil Al-Araby, Chair of the Arab League, participated in a discussion on Syria with UK representatives at the United Nations General Assembly on 30 September. We remain committed to engagement and coordination with regional partners in our efforts to degrade Daesh in Syria.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-12-03T16:53:45.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432845/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432845/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-11-26","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what discussions he has had with the Arab League on the situation in Syria before he published his response to the Second Report from the Foreign Affairs Committee, on the Extension of Offensive British Military Operations to Syria, HC 457.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432846","Prime Minister","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Financial Actions Task Force (FATF) report on ‘Financing of the Terrorist Organisation ISIL’ (Feb 2015) sets out specific measures which countries should adopt, over and above general measures designed to block terrorist financing, to ensure Daesh cannot access the international financial system. The FATF conducted a report for the G20 Leaders in November 2015 on implementation. They found almost all 194 jurisdictions had criminalised terrorist financing and 90% of jurisdictions had a legal framework to enforce sanctions. There were 33 jurisdictions which had secured convictions for terrorist financing.</p><br /><p>The Egmont Group comprises 151 members, including the UK, USA, France and regional partners such as Saudi Arabia, Turkey, Qatar and Lebanon. In June 2015 the Group expanded its membership; 42 new bilateral agreements to exchange information were announced to help combat global money laundering and terrorist threats. The Group also issued a communication to its members in June 2015 regarding Daesh which encouraged members to use its unique global network to combat Daesh money laundering and financing by increasing international cooperation, including the exchange of information.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-12-03T16:58:36.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432846/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432846/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-11-26","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, with reference to pages 12 and 13 of his response to the Second Report from the Foreign Affairs Select Committee, on the Extension of Offensive Military Operations to Syria, HC 457, what specific steps have been taken through the Financial Action Task Force and Egmont Groups to block funding of ISIS.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432847","Scotland Office","false","2015-12-03","<p>Spending Review 2015 set out settlements for departments and showed how the government will deliver on its priorities, eliminate the deficit, and deliver security and opportunity for working people. Final decisions on internal departmental funding allocations for future years, including for research and development, have not yet been made.</p><br />","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-12-03T11:30:39.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432847/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432847/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-11-26","Scotland Office: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much of his Department's funding allocated in the Comprehensive Spending Review 2015 will be for research and development expenditure up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","17774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432848","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>Spending Review 2015 set out settlements for departments and showed how the government will deliver on its priorities, eliminate the deficit, and deliver security and opportunity for working people.</p><br /><p>Final decisions on internal departmental funding allocations for future years, including for research and development, have not yet been made.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-12-04T13:10:34.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432848/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432848/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432848/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Department for Transport: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much of his Department's funding allocated in the Spending Review 2015 will be for research and development expenditure up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","17775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432849","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-01","<p>The Government is currently considering the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report before taking any decisions on next steps.</p><br /><p>The Government will carefully consider all the evidence set out, including that on costs, when making a decision on additional runway capacity.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-12-01T15:17:50.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432849/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432849/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","London Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent comparative assessment he has made of the cost to the public purse of expanding (a) Heathrow and (b) Gatwick airports.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Turner","Isle of Wight","Mr Andrew Turner","17831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432850","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>The Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) has published a Safety Notice which provides guidance on laser attacks, including the action that aircraft crew and controllers should take during and immediately after a laser attack. It also includes a self-assessment tool to help those exposed to lasers to make an immediate assessment of their vision and determine whether or not they need to consult an eye specialist.</p><br /><p>The CAA is also co-ordinating an industry-wide initiative to decide what further measures might be needed to reduce the risk of an accident arising from the misuse of lasers. As part of this process, the CAA is working with a wide range of key stakeholders including relevant Government Departments, emergency services, air traffic control, airports, and airlines.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-12-04T13:37:52.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432850/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432850/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Aviation: Lasers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what guidance his Department has issued to the aviation industry on ensuring the safety of pilots by their avoiding the illegal use of lasers from the ground.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","17841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432851","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>Work was undertaken to assess the signage before the launch of Dart Charge in November 2014, with fifty new signs unveiled ahead of its introduction.</p><br /><p>The initial compliance rate is 92.6% which compares favourably with other similar schemes and indicates strong awareness levels among drivers. However Highways England continue to monitor feedback from customers to see if any enhancements can be made.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-12-04T13:43:52.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432851/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432851/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Dartford-Thurrock Crossing: Tolls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the adequacy of signage for the Dart Charge in effectively informing users about that charge.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","17842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432852","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-01","<p>The Department for Transport does not collect this information.</p><br /><p>However, I am able to say that the British Transport Police will shortly be launching Project Servator, which aims to detect and deter crime on the railways. It deploys highly visible and unpredictable police patrols to prevent a range of criminal activity, from pickpocketing and theft to more serious crimes including terrorism.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","17851","2015-12-01T16:40:32.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432852/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432852/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Public Transport: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many assaults there have been on staff working for (a) London Underground, (b) London Overground, (c) London buses, (d) Docklands Light Railway and (e) Tramlink in each year between 2010 and 2014.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","17850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432853","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-01","<p>The Department for Transport does not collect this information.</p><br /><p>However, I am able to say that the British Transport Police will shortly be launching Project Servator, which aims to detect and deter crime on the railways. It deploys highly visible and unpredictable police patrols to prevent a range of criminal activity, from pickpocketing and theft to more serious crimes including terrorism.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","17850","2015-12-01T16:40:32.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432853/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432853/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Public Transport: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many assaults there have been on staff working for (a) London Underground, (b) London Overground, (c) London buses, (d) Docklands Light Railway and (e) Tramlink in October of each year between 2010 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","17851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432854","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-01","<p>The introduction and roll-out of part-time season tickets will give people who commute part-time a better deal than they currently have access to. We have challenged the rail industry to develop proposals for pricing and delivering more flexible season tickets for those who work or commute part-time which could also attract new customers onto the railway.</p><br /><p>Progress on delivery of more flexible tickets is beginning to be made. Govia Thameslink Railway (GTR) have a franchise commitment to introduce carnet style tickets on their smartcards which is subject to the Secretary of State’s approval.</p><br /><p>A number of costed options are being reviewed and a pilot programme has been developed, benefitting from and delivering the Key smart ticketing capability, this is expected to be introduced in May 2016.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-12-01T15:11:02.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432854/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432854/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Thameslink Railway Line: Season Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to paragraph 2.82, page 94 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, what progress his Department has made on introducing flexible season tickets on the Govia Thameslink Railway franchise.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","17812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432855","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>The North of England Electrification Task Force placed the Calder Valley Line in the top tier of lines it recommended for future electrification. Network Rail is currently updating its national electrification strategy, which will include the Calder Valley line, and will take the Task Force’s recommendations into account. The updated strategy will be subject to public consultation during 2016 and inform the Government’s strategy for Rail for 2019-2024.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-12-04T13:31:45.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432855/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432855/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432855/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the schemes recommended for prioritisation in the report of the Rail North Electrification Task Force, published in March 2015; and if he will prioritise electrification of the Calder Valley rail line.","false","Biography information for Holly Lynch","Halifax","Holly Lynch","17965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432856","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>The Government is currently considering the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report before taking any decisions on next steps.</p><br /><p>The Government will carefully consider all the evidence set out when making a decision on additional runway capacity.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-12-04T13:05:28.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432856/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432856/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432856/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Aviation: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what relative weight he plans to give to (a) deliverability and (b) affordability in assessing the option for increasing aviation capacity in the South East; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Ansell","Eastbourne","Caroline Ansell","18008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432857","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>Initial discussions on the 2015 People Survey results for the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) have taken place in senior management fora. Further discussions are planned, including within existing DVSA governance arrangements.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>The Department for Transport officials have been working closely with the management side at DVSA to try to resolve the industrial dispute, and to help ensure that the disruption to public services is kept to a minimum. The Permanent Secretary for Transport has written twice to the unions since the dispute began urging them to suspend their action and return to discussions with DVSA management.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-12-04T13:51:27.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432857/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432857/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432857/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency: Job Satisfaction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions his Department has had with the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency on (a) that agency's staff survey results and (b) recent industrial action affecting that agency; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","17963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432858","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>The introduction and roll-out of part-time season tickets will give people who commute part-time a better deal than they currently have access to. We have challenged the rail industry to develop proposals for pricing and delivering more flexible season tickets for those who work or commute part-time which could also attract new customers onto the railway.</p><br /><p>We are making progress on delivering more flexible tickets. For example, Govia Thameslink Railway (GTR) have a franchise commitment to introduce carnet style tickets on their smartcards which is subject to the Secretary of State’s approval. We expect GTR to meet its obligations and are working with them to ensure they are delivered.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-12-04T13:02:18.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432858/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432858/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432858/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-26","Railways: Season Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress he has made on the introduction of flexible rail season tickets; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Ansell","Eastbourne","Caroline Ansell","17990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432859","Wales Office","false","2015-12-03","<p>I have regular meetings with the Chancellor of the Exchequer, which provide opportunities to discuss a range of issues, including matters related to funding of services across Wales.</p><p>The Government is committed to Welsh language programming and to the future of S4C. The majority of S4C’s funding comes via the BBC and last week's spending review settlement on the Government element of S4C's funding therefore represents a modest reduction in its overall funding.</p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb",,"2015-12-03T12:59:24.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432859/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432859/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432859/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-11-26","S4C: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, if he will meet the Chancellor of the Exchequer to discuss the effect of the reductions in funding to S4C proposed in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015.","false","Biography information for Susan Elan Jones","Clwyd South","Susan Elan Jones","17789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432860","Wales Office","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Wales Office allocates no funding specifically for research and development. The Department funds research and development on a case by case basis, and any future spend will be met from within the Department’s overall spending review settlement.</p><br />","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2015-12-03T15:47:13.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432860/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432860/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432860/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-11-26","Wales Office: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how much of his Department's funding allocated in the Spending Review 2015 will be for research and development expenditure up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","17777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432861","Women and Equalities","false","2015-12-04","<p>The Spending Review set out settlements for departments and showed how the government will deliver on its priorities, eliminate the deficit, and deliver security and opportunity for working people.</p><br /><p>Final decisions on internal departmental funding allocations for future years, including for research and development, have not yet been made.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-12-04T14:22:31.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432861/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432861/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432861/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2015-11-26","Government Equalities Office: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, how much of the Government Equalities Office's funding allocated in the Spending Review 2015 will be for research and development expenditure up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","17766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432862","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-02","<p>Spending Review 2015 set out settlements for departments and showed how the government will deliver on its priorities, eliminate the deficit, and deliver security and opportunity for working people.</p><br /><p>Final decisions on internal departmental funding allocations for future years, including for research and development, have not yet been made.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-02T14:29:17.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432862/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432862/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432862/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Department for Work and Pensions: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much of his Department's funding allocated in the Spending Review 2015 will be for research and development expenditure up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","17778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432863","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>DWP operates the standard Civil Service whistleblowing policy, but the Department’s procedures go further by also enabling staff to raise concerns via a dedicated hotline operated by an Internal Investigations team.</p><br /><p>DWP is committed to ensuring high standards of conduct in all that it does. For civil servants, these standards are reinforced by the Civil Service Code and the Department’s Standards of Behaviour.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-01T15:26:29.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432863/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432863/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432863/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Jobcentre Plus: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what procedure his Department has for responding to whistle-blowing reports from staff at Jobcentre Plus.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","17852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432864","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>Automatic enrolment has been a great success to date, with 5.57 million people automatically enrolled into a workplace pension by 67,892 employers.</p><p>From June 2015 onwards, small and micro employers with 49 or less workers began enrolling all eligible workers into a qualifying workplace pension scheme.</p><br /><p>We remain on track to complete the roll out of automatic enrolment to all employers from 2012 to 2018.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-01T15:30:05.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432864/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432864/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432864/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Occupational Pensions: Small Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress he has made on pensions auto-enrolment to small and micro businesses; and if he plans to complete that auto-enrolment for those businesses by 2018.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","17853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432865","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>Existing claimants, whether in the work-related activity group or the support group, who undergo a work capability assessment after April 2017 and are placed in, or remain in, the work-related activity group, will continue to receive the work-related activity component.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-01T15:04:16.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432865/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432865/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432865/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether it is his policy that a claimant of employment and support allowance (ESA) in the Support Group who transfers to the Work Related Activity Group will receive the current rate of ESA, as an existing claimant, or the reduced rate of ESA proposed in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","17829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432866","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>We are committed to ensuring all claimants receive the best possible support. All policies are kept under review to ensure this is the case.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-01T14:58:45.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432866/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432866/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432866/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will establish a team in his Department to champion the interests  of universal credit claimants as recommended in the report entitled Waiting for Credit: the delivery of universal credit experienced by Citizens Advice Bureau claimants in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","17813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432867","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost</p><p><em></em></p><p><em></em></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","17883 ; 17941 ; 18029","2015-12-01T14:50:54.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432867/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432867/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432867/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the potential effect on the income of a family with one earner and two children that starts a claim for universal credit and is not migrating from a legacy benefit of the proposed reforms to universal credit in the Summer Budget 2015 in (a) 2016-17, (b) 2017-18, (c) 2018-19 and (d) 2019-10.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","17882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432868","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost</p><p><em></em></p><p><em></em></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","17882 ; 17941 ; 18029","2015-12-01T14:50:54.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432868/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432868/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432868/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the potential effect on the income of a family with one earner and three children that starts a new claim for universal credit and is not migrating from a legacy benefit of the proposed reforms to universal credit in the Summer Budget 2015 in (a) 2016-17, (b) 2017-18, (c) 2018-19 and (d) 2019-10.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","17883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432869","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>Customers living abroad and in receipt of payments delivered by the Department for Work and Pensions can have their payments made either:</p><br /><ul><li>Direct into a UK bank or building society account in sterling; or</li><li>Direct into an overseas account in the local currency;</li></ul><br /><p>All payments made to overseas customers, whether in sterling or local currency, are subject to fluctuating exchange rates. However, for payments made directly to overseas accounts in the relevant local currency, the Department has negotiated a competitive exchange rate which is more favourable that that available on the open Market.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-01T15:11:10.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432869/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432869/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432869/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the potential merits of the use of alternative currencies for benefits payments.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","17885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432870","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-04","<p>The table below represents the number of successful convictions in Wales since April 2012.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>No of Convictions</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012 – 2013</p></td><td><p>1616</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013 – 2014</p></td><td><p>1512</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014 – 2015</p></td><td><p>992</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>The data held for the number of convictions prior to 2012 is not available for publication.</p><br /><p>The information requested for Wrexham is not readily available. This is because the data is not collated in a format for Wrexham only. This information could only be provided by examining individual investigation files. This could only be conducted at disproportionate time and cost.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-04T10:04:22.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432870/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432870/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432870/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Social Security Benefits: Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many cases of benefit fraud that led to convictions were prosecuted in (a) Wales and (b) Wrexham in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","17874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432871","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-04","<p>All personal care assistants that meet the eligibility criteria for automatic enrolment will be automatically enrolled into a pension scheme by their employer. In order to be eligible, staff must be between 22 and State Pension age and must earn more than £10,000 per year (which is £192 per week).</p><br /> <br /><p>We are working with The Pensions Regulator to ensure that employers of personal care assistants are supported with their automatic enrolment duties. The Regulator has tailored its online Step by Step guide and offline communications specifically to employers of personal care assistants. Furthermore, the Regulator provides information that will help employers of personal care assistants to choose a pension scheme. Finally, the Regulator has a dedicated Industry Liaison team who engage with providers, employers, intermediaries, charities and user-led organisations to raise awareness and understanding of automatic enrolment.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-04T09:55:05.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432871/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432871/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432871/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Carers: Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the number of personal assistants who provide care to people formerly in receipt of the Independent Living Fund who will be entitled to pension scheme auto-enrolment; and what guidance his Department has issued to employers of such employees on that matter.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","18007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432872","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>Universal Credit entitlement is assessed and paid in arrears. Payment is made on a fixed date 7 days after the end of the monthly assessment period.</p><br /><p>Where a claimant’s earnings or income is insufficient to meet their living costs and in order to safeguard against financial hardship before the first UC payment, an advance payment of up to 50% of their UC award may be made.</p><p>Personal Budgeting Support advice is also available to all claimants.</p><br /> <br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-01T17:17:42.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432872/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432872/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432872/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how long it takes for the average claimant to receive a first payment of universal credit from the time they became unemployed in those areas where universal credit has been introduced.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","17942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432873","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>This policy was introduced because in some areas the increases in social rents have outstripped the increases in private rents.</p><br /><p>This policy will cap social sector rents at the relevant Local Housing Allowance rate for the area, but will only apply from April 2018 where a new tenancy is taken out or a tenancy is renewed after April 2016. By only applying the cap when a new tenancy is taken on or an existing tenancy is renewed will mean that claimants will have the opportunity to consider whether they can afford to take on the property before committing to the tenancy.</p><br /><p>The Discretionary Housing Payment scheme will be available for those living in accommodation that has been purpose built or significantly adapted to meet the needs of a disabled person, in the same way as it is for those who receive a reduction in their eligible rent for the removal of the spare room subsidy.</p><br /> <br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-01T15:53:52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432873/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432873/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Housing Benefit: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the reductions in housing benefit announced in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015 on claimants who receive housing benefit for housing that has been purpose-built for disabled people.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","18003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432874","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-01","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost</p><p><em></em></p><p><em></em></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","17882 ; 17883 ; 17941","2015-12-01T14:50:54.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432874/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432874/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432874/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-26","Universal Credit: Oldham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many (a) disabled people and (b) families with children will experience a reduction in universal credit in 2016-17 as a result of changes to the work allowance in (i) Oldham Local Authority area, (ii) Oldham East and Saddleworth constituency and (iii) Oldham West and Royton constituency.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","18029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436137","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>We are committed to expanding NCS, which is why the Chancellor announced our ambition that 300,000 young people participate in NCS every year by 2019/20 so that they can learn new skills and give back to their communities.</p><p>We take great care to ensure that all young people, regardless of background, can take part, providing bursaries and additional support where necessary.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-12-09T17:00:06.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436137/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436137/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436137/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that all young people who wish to participate in the National Citizen Service are able to do so.","false","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","902479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436532","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>We are committed to expanding NCS, which is why the Chancellor announced our ambition that 300,000 young people participate in NCS every year by 2019/20 so that they can learn new skills and give back to their communities.</p><p>We take great care to ensure that all young people, regardless of background, can take part, providing bursaries and additional support where necessary.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-12-09T16:59:43.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436532/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436532/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436532/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that all young people who wish to participate in the National Citizen Service are able to do so.","false","Biography information for Martin Vickers","Cleethorpes","Martin Vickers","902482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436534","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>We are committed to the Freedom of Information Act. An independent commission was established review the workings of the Act. The Government will consider the Commission’s report when it is received.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-09T17:58:14.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436534/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436534/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans he has to bring forward legislative proposals to amend the Freedom of Information Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","902477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436536","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>It should be a source of pride that the Civil Service has successfully changed the way it operates and become more efficient - it is now delivering far more, for less, than it did before 2010. It is a tribute to the dedication and work of individual Civil Servants that job satisfaction remains high and wellbeing has increased.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-09T17:56:33.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436536/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436536/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436536/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to improve the morale of staff within the civil service.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","902481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436538","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>In May 2010 the deficit between government revenue and public spending was the largest percentage of GDP of any developed country. As part of our long-term economic plan to ensure the country lives within its means, we took action to drive efficiency from day one.</p><p>By 2014/15 the Government had saved £18.6 billion through efficiency and reform, and tackling fraud, error and uncollected debt (against a 2009/10 baseline). At a very conservative estimate this is equivalent to £850 for each working household across Britain.</p><p>The £18.6 billion saving includes £6.1 billion by improving how government buys goods and services and £1.5 billion by transforming how government works, including putting services and transactions online and rationalising the government’s property portfolio - releasing government land, by moving to shared property and using less office space, enables land to be released which can be put to better economic use.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-09T17:57:22.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436538/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436538/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Government Departments: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to implement efficiency savings across government departments.","false","Biography information for Sir Simon Burns","Chelmsford","Sir Simon Burns","902475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436540","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>In the last five years the number of registered charities has increased by over 2,000, and the sector’s annual income has grown by over £10bn.</p><p /> <p>Looking ahead, the Government’s priority is supporting a strong, independent, transparent and accountable voluntary sector. Plans will include a focus on outcomes based commissioning, restoring public trust in fundraising and strengthening the Charity Commission to protect charities from abuse through the Charities Bill.</p><br />","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-12-09T16:59:18.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436540/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436540/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans he has to support charities during this Parliament.","false","Biography information for Bob Blackman","Harrow East","Bob Blackman","902473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436541","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>Modernising the law governing Trade Unions will improve industrial relations. We have already seen the benefits in the Civil Service of reforming facility time, where we have delivered a saving to the taxpayer of over £52million, and the majority of departments have removed the outdated system of collecting union dues by check off. These benefits will now be delivered across the public sector.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-09T17:57:07.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436541/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436541/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436541/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Civil Service: Industrial Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the provisions in the Trade Union Bill on industrial relations within the civil service.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","902480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436542","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>We expect all policy making to take account of the needs of all parts of the UK, including Wales, and continue to build up our policy making capability to do so. The government fully recognises the importance of the Welsh language in providing services to citizens. For Cabinet Office, the priority is to make sure that GOV.UK carries high quality Welsh content and to provide the tools for other parts of government to publish in both languages.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-09T17:56:50Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436542/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436542/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-26","Welsh Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to ensure that the Welsh language is taken into account in his Department's policy development processes.","false","Biography information for Glyn Davies","Montgomeryshire","Glyn Davies","902478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432168","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-03","<p>My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Transport and I agree about the vital contribution of road and rail infrastructure to national and local economic growth and resilience. In the Spending Review, the government committed to £7.2 billion of transport investment in the South West, including projects with benefits for the Heart of the South West area such as the £2 billion investment to dual the A303. The government also confirmed that:</p><ul><li>Projects such as the North Devon Link Road will be able to bid for the new £475 million Local Majors Fund.</li><li>It is investing £20 million in the New Stations Fund, which will look at bids including the proposal for a stop between Castle Cary to Taunton.</li><li>The new South Western rail franchise will incentivise bidders to increase capacity and improve passenger satisfaction.</li><li>Existing £195.5m Growth Deal commitments, including transport infrastructure, have been confirmed.</li></ul>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-12-03T14:24:51.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432168/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432168/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-25","Transport: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Transport on the contribution of further investment in road and rail infrastructure to economic growth and resilience in the Heart of the South West Local Enterprise Partnership area.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Pow","Taunton Deane","Rebecca Pow","17570"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432169","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-01","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-12-01T17:01:44.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432169/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432169/answer","17612 table FINAL.xlsx ; 17612 FINAL.pdf","17612 table FINAL.xlsx ; 17612 FINAL.pdf","Excel Attachment for Member - Datasets ; UKSA Letter to Member - Datasets","Excel Attachment for Member - Datasets ; UKSA Letter to Member - Datasets","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432169/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-25","Statistics of Trade Act 1947","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what datasets are collected under the provisions of the Statistics of Trade Act 1947.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","17612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432170","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-04","<p><strong></strong></p><br /><p>My Rt hon Friend the Chancellor of the Exchequer published the results of the Spending Review on 25th November. This is a good settlement for FE. Between 2010-11 and 2019-20 government will have doubled spending on apprenticeships in cash terms to £2.5 billion, including income from the new apprenticeship levy and protecting funding for the core adult skills participation budgets in cash terms, at £1.5 billion</p><br /><p>The Government will make £362 million of savings and efficiencies from adult skills funding by 2019-20. We are prioritising funding for participation, with savings being made from supporting budgets. We are also restructuring the sector through locally-led Area Reviews to provide sustainable and high quality provision in the future.</p><br /> <br />","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-12-04T14:58:55.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432170/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432170/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432170/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-25","Adult Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Spending Review 2015, what savings and efficiencies he will make from the adult skills budget by 2019-20; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","17689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432171","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Departments and their agencies will undertake this work with no additional staffing. Additional costs will be minimal. The Departments and agencies have re-prioritised from within existing resources to accommodate the additional work, including providing access to additional advice and support from further education and six form colleges Advisers.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-12-09T10:37:31.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432171/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432171/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432171/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-25","Further Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 24 November 2015 to Question 16786, what estimate he has made of the (a) total, (b) staffing and (c) resources cost of conducting area-based reviews of post-16 education and training institutions.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","17719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432172","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-04","<p>To improve transparency, the Department has established a publicly accessible central register of people with significant control (PSC register) through the Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Act 2015.</p><p>The PSC register will be an easily accessible single source of information about the ultimate owners and controllers of UK companies, Limited Liability Partnerships and Societas Europeae. From June 2016, these corporate entities will be required to make their beneficial ownership information publically available through the UK register of companies.</p><p>It is already a legal requirement that the name of each of the partners of limited partnerships be submitted to Companies House on registration. This information is available to the public free of charge through the new Companies House beta service. Companies House also works collaboratively with other government departments and agencies to tackle crime and fraud, including money laundering.</p><p>We are currently considering the scope of the UK register to ensure we comply with the European Union’s Fourth Money Laundering Directive, which requires corporate and other legal entities to obtain and hold beneficial ownership information.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-12-04T11:38:20.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432172/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432172/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432172/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-25","Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what mechanisms are in place to ensure transparency of the ownership of limited partnerships; what plans he has to (a) improve such transparency and (b) ensure that such partnerships are not set up for money laundering purposes; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","17732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432173","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-04","<p>The UK is participating in discussions with the Commission and other Member States on possible options and approaches towards handling the Commission’s request, regarding the termination of these treaties. These discussions are at an early stage and no consensus has been reached among Member States.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-12-04T14:26:30.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432173/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432173/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432173/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-25","Investment: Treaties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what his policy is on the European Commission's request of 18 June 2015 to five EU member states to terminate intra-EU bilateral investment treaties.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","17742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432174","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-30","<p>The principal feature of the Interpretative Notice is a recommendation that goods imported into the EU which originate from Israeli settlements in the territories occupied by Israel since 1967 should bear an indication which makes that provenance clear. That recommendation was included in technical advice to UK retailers and importers concerning labelling agricultural produce from the West Bank that was issued by Defra in 2009. We are currently in discussion with other Departments to consider whether revisions need to be made to the 2009 advice in the light of the Interpretative Notice. As regards sanctions and penalties for mis-labelling, these are dealt with in various pieces of legislation depending on the goods concerned.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-11-30T17:36:37.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432174/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432174/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432174/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-11-25","EU External Trade: Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department is taking to (a) enforce the European Commission Interpretative Notice, C2015 7834 final, on the indication of origin of goods from territories occupied by Israel since June 1967 and (b) ensure that penalties for mis-labeling of such products are effective, proportionate and dissuasive.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","17755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432175","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-30","<p>Workforce planning and redeployment pools are the responsibility of each individual Department to determine and manage. The numbers in redeployment pools is under constant change and therefore this information is not held centrally.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-30T13:01:08.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432175/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432175/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-25","Civil Servants: Labour Mobility","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many civil servants in each Department are in the redeployment pool.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","17629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432176","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-30","<p>We are committed to publishing data in a timely fashion, and further transparency data will be published in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-30T13:01:47.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432176/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432176/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-25","Government Departments: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to ensure regular publication of departmental transparency data.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","17600"
