"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432198","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-02","<p>The Northern Ireland Executive’s block grant allocations for the Spending Review period were set out at the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015. The allocations were calculated by the application of the Barnett Formula to UK government departmental settlements in the normal way.</p><br /><p>Further information regarding the Barnett Formula can be found in HM Treasury’s ‘Statement of Funding Policy’.</p><br />","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-12-02T16:30:54.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432198/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432198/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-25","Public Expenditure: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the Barnett consequentials are for Northern Ireland of the measures announced in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","17744"
