 Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","17713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432216","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>As a result of Spending Review 2015 the Ministry of Defence will reduce its annual transport expenditure over the Spending Review period. The estimated savings from this measure are around £25 million per year.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T16:46:31.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432216/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432216/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Ministry of Defence: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the savings to his Department from planned reductions in travel expenditure in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432217","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Designing and building submarines is one of the largest programmes and one of the most complex activities that the Ministry of Defence and UK Industry has ever undertaken. It is the purpose of a design phase to improve our understanding of costs and timescales, which we have now done. The current estimates reflect what we have learned since the design phase began.</p><p>As stated in the Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR) 2015 (Cm9161), our latest estimate of the total cost to manufacture the four Successor submarines reflects greater maturity of the design and understanding of the supply chain, amounts to £31 billion; we will also set a contingency of £10 billion. This level of contingency represents about 35% of the costs to completion and is a prudent estimate based on past experience of large, complex projects.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17736 ; 17895 ; 17897","2015-12-03T16:21:00.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432217/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432217/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Nuclear Submarines: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons the latest estimate of the cost of the Successor class submarine programme has increased to £31 billion; and whether he expects that cost to rise.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432218","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<br /><br /><p>Defence expenditure on fees for professional services in each of the last five financial years (FY) is provided below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>Professional Fees</strong> <strong>£ millions</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><br>718</p></td><td><p><br>497</p></td><td><p><br>354</p></td><td><p><br>308</p></td><td><p><br>316</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>The increase in expenditure from FY 2013-14 is mainly attributable to the Defence Equipment and Support (DE&amp;S) organisation spending on Private Sector Support (PSS). PSS provides DE&amp;S with critical technical support, while also using that support to design and develop the tools and processes required to upskill staff and transform the organisation.</p><br /><p>Expenditure on PSS (£227 million in FY 2014-15 included in the table above) was previously assigned to the Equipment Programme, but moved to the Professional Services category following the creation of the Bespoke Trading Entity.</p><br /><br /> <br /> <br /><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-04T14:25:19.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432218/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432218/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Ministry of Defence: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent from the public purse on professional fees in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432219","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>As a result of Spending Review 2015 the Ministry of Defence will reduce its annual expenditure on fees for professional services over the Spending Review period. The estimated savings from this measure are around £29 million per year.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-30T17:31:12.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432219/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432219/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Ministry of Defence: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of savings to the public purse expected through the reduction in professional fees paid out by his Department in the 2015-16 financial year and in each of the next five such years.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432220","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<br /><p>The estimated military paybill saving in 2015-16 from pay restraint is £98 million.</p><br /><p>The Summer Budget confirmed that the Government would fund public sector pay awards at 1% for four years from 2016-17 onwards. The estimated military pay saving is £1.8 billion over the next five years as detailed below.</p><p>Figures are all in £millions.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017-18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018-19</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2019-20</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2020-21</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p><br></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>80</p></td><td><p>180</p></td><td><p>366</p></td><td><p>602</p></td><td><p>625</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Commitment bonuses which have not proven effective are to be withdrawn in full with effect from 1 April 2021. The estimated saving from ending commitment bonuses is £118 million over the next five years as detailed below.</p><p>Figures are all in £millions.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2016-17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017-18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018-19</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2019-20</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2020-21</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p><br></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>35</p></td><td><p>48</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T17:04:22.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432220/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432220/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the projected savings for his Department arising from military pay restraint in the 2015-16 financial year and in each of the next five such years; and what proportion of those savings will arise from (a) pay rises limited to one per cent and (b) the ending of military commitment bonuses.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432221","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>The civilian staff reductions announced as part of the Strategic Defence and Security Review will be managed in a number of different ways. In the short term, the Ministry of Defence has agreed to make further savings and adjustments in this current financial year as part of the Government’s commitment to reducing the deficit. This is still on-going and may mean restrictions on recruitment.</p><p>Over the longer term, a number of change programmes already under way across the Department are reducing our civilian workforce. These programmes will continue, and individuals are already aware if they are affected. We will also drive forward programmes to consider better ways of delivering services, and explore opportunities to deliver outputs in more efficient or innovative ways.</p><p>We are confident these programmes will deliver the required reductions to meet the efficiency and reform savings announced in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","17735 ; 17752","2015-11-30T16:59:16.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432221/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432221/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the planned reductions in current staff numbers in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, how many of those job reductions will be in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17, (c) 2017-18, (d) 2018-19, (e) 2019-20 and (f) 2020-21; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432222","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>A number of change programmes are already under way to reduce Ministry of Defence civilian workforce numbers. The remaining savings will be made through new studies that will identify opportunities for more efficient and innovative ways of working.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T17:04:40.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432222/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432222/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Ministry of Defence: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the cost of redundancy payments arising from meeting the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 target of reducing civilian staff numbers by 41,000.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432223","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>We were already planning to deliver efficiency savings in the equipment budget as outlined in the Defence Equipment Plan 2015 published on 22 October 2015, available in the Library of The House.</p><p>Following the Spending Review and Strategic Defence and Security Review (Cm9161), the total amount of equipment efficiency savings we plan to make is equivalent to 3% of the equipment budget in 2016-17 rising to 6% of the equipment budget by 2020-21.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:37:35.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432223/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432223/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Defence Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the level of potential efficiency in the equipment budget in (a) 2015-16, (b) 2016-17, (c) 2017-18, (d) 2018-19, (e) 2019-20 and (f) 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432224","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>The civilian staff reductions announced as part of the Strategic Defence and Security Review will be managed in a number of different ways. In the short term, the Ministry of Defence has agreed to make further savings and adjustments in this current financial year as part of the Government’s commitment to reducing the deficit. This is still on-going and may mean restrictions on recruitment.</p><p>Over the longer term, a number of change programmes already under way across the Department are reducing our civilian workforce. These programmes will continue, and individuals are already aware if they are affected. We will also drive forward programmes to consider better ways of delivering services, and explore opportunities to deliver outputs in more efficient or innovative ways.</p><p>We are confident these programmes will deliver the required reductions to meet the efficiency and reform savings announced in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","17733 ; 17752","2015-11-30T16:59:16.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432224/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432224/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's planned savings in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, what plans he has to reduce the number of civilian staff in his Department.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432225","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<br /><p>The estimated Ministry of Defence (MOD) civilian paybill saving in 2015-16 from pay restraint is £10 million.</p><p>The Summer Budget confirmed that the Government would fund public sector pay awards at 1% for four years from 2016-17 onwards.</p><p>The estimated saving for MOD civilians from this pay restraint is £254 million over the next five years as detailed below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong><br>2016-17</strong> <strong>(£ million)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong><br>2017-18</strong> <strong>(£ million)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong><br>2018-19</strong> <strong>(£ million)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong><br>2019-20</strong> <strong>(£ million)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong><br>2020-21</strong> <strong>(£ million)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>26</p></td><td><p>52</p></td><td><p>92</p></td><td><p>77</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T17:02:39.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432225/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432225/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Ministry of Defence: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of projected savings in his Department arising from the imposition of civilian pay restraint in the 2015-16 financial year and each of the next five such years.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432226","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>This Government has no plans to remove incremental pay or annual pay increases for serving members of the Armed Forces.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-11-30T16:54:23.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432226/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432226/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he plans to change the payment of annual increments to military staff between 2015-16 and 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432227","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Designing and building submarines is one of the largest programmes and one of the most complex activities that the Ministry of Defence and UK Industry has ever undertaken. It is the purpose of a design phase to improve our understanding of costs and timescales, which we have now done. The current estimates reflect what we have learned since the design phase began.</p><p>As stated in the Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR) 2015 (Cm9161), our latest estimate of the total cost to manufacture the four Successor submarines reflects greater maturity of the design and understanding of the supply chain, amounts to £31 billion; we will also set a contingency of £10 billion. This level of contingency represents about 35% of the costs to completion and is a prudent estimate based on past experience of large, complex projects.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","17739 ; 17895 ; 17897","2015-12-03T16:21:00.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432227/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432227/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Nuclear Submarines: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons the projected in-service date for the first of the Successor class submarines has been delayed by two years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432228","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>The civilian staff reductions announced as part of the Strategic Defence and Security Review will be managed in a number of different ways. In the short term, the Ministry of Defence has agreed to make further savings and adjustments in this current financial year as part of the Government’s commitment to reducing the deficit. This is still on-going and may mean restrictions on recruitment.</p><p>Over the longer term, a number of change programmes already under way across the Department are reducing our civilian workforce. These programmes will continue, and individuals are already aware if they are affected. We will also drive forward programmes to consider better ways of delivering services, and explore opportunities to deliver outputs in more efficient or innovative ways.</p><p>We are confident these programmes will deliver the required reductions to meet the efficiency and reform savings announced in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","17733 ; 17735","2015-11-30T16:59:16.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432228/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432228/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the reduction in civilian headcount in his Department required to meet the efficiency and reform savings announced in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015 for the 2015-16 financial year and in each of the next five such years.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432229","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 (Cm 9161) set out the range of capabilities that, taken together, will sustain and enhance our ability to fulfil Defence's contribution to UK National Security.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-03T16:37:05.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432229/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432229/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 80 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, what the 170 investments to sustain and enhance defence capabilities are.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","17737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432230","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>I will place a copy of the 2015-16 Civilian Manpower Capitation Rates in the Library of the House, subject to the redaction of personal information. The 2015-16 rates will be available early in 2016, their compilation being determined by the timing of the relevant annual pay reviews.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T16:59:43.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432230/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432230/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432230/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of the Civilian Manpower Capitation rates for 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","17729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432231","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>The review was a study undertaken to understand how best to deliver Adventurous Training to meet the future needs of the RAF and not a financially driven initiative, therefore the principles of JSP 507 were followed although a formal Investment Appraisal was not undertaken.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T16:47:09.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432231/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432231/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the assessment procedure to close (a) MOD Fairbourne and (b) MOD Llanrwst followed investment appraisal on project evaluation policy JSP507; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432232","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>Historical data on the number of students and cost per trainee that took part in adventurous training, at any of the centres, from 2005 to 2010 is not held.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T16:47:58.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432232/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432232/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many training courses have been completed at (a) MOD Greytown-on-Spey, (b) MOD Llanwrst, (c) MOD Fairbourne and (d) MOD Crickhowell in each year from 2005 to 2010; how many students of each service attended each such course; what the cost of each such course was per trainee; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432233","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>I assume the hon. Member is referring to the Force Development and Adventurous Training Review. Whilst the provision of adventurous training for the whole force concept was one of the many factors in the Review, we do not hold documents principally about the whole force concept.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-11-30T17:05:15.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432233/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432233/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432233/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library all documents relating to the delivery of a system of force development and adventurous training with a contingent whole force construct relating to (a) MOD Greytown-on-Spey, (b) MOD Llanwrst, (c) MOD Fairbourne and (d) MOD Crickhowell; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432234","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-30","<p>The Defence Equipment Plan 2015, placed in the Library of the House on 22 October 2015, set out our plans, before the Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR) 2015, for spending £166 billion on defence equipment and support over the next 10 years.</p><p>In the SDSR we set out our plans for additional investment in Armed Forces defence equipment and support. This includes improving Special Forces' capabilities, procuring three new Fleet Solid Support ships and investing in a fleet of nine Boeing P-8 Maritime Patrol Aircraft.</p><p>Following the SDSR, we now plan to spend £178 billion on defence equipment and support over the next 10 years.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-30T16:51:11.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432234/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432234/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432234/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 4.34 of the National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence Review 2015 and to his Department's press release dated 23 November 2015, what equipment and support (a) was to be procured with the £166 billion programme and (b) will be procured under the £178 billion programme.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","17722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432235","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-04T14:16:28.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432235/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432235/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average accommodation and travel costs relating to training at (a) MOD Grantown-on-Spey, (b) MOD Llanwrst, (c) MOD Fairbourne (d) MOD Crickhowell were in each of the last 10 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432236","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>RAF personnel are set generic Leadership, Management, Air Power, Communication, Force Protection, Ethos, Military Skills and Organisational objectives. Training delivered at the Force Development Adventurous Training Centres helps deliver these objectives.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-02T16:18:32.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432236/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432236/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what specialist skills and opportunities were available to trainees at (a) MOD Grantown-on-Spey, (b) MOD Llanwrst, (c) MOD Fairbourne, (d) MOD Crickhowell were in each of the last 10 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432237","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<br /><p>The Eagles Scheme was developed in 2008 to utilise adventurous training and staff rides to enhance ethos, communication skills, leadership and management skills. Although historic records on attendance are not held centrally, the aim for financial year 2015-16 is to deliver courses to 5,000 personnel as follows:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Training Centre</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Approx No of trainees</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Force Development Training Centre (FDTC) Bavaria</p></td><td><p>1,900</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>FDTC Grantown on Spey</p></td><td><p>500</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>FDTC Crickhowell</p></td><td><p>500</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>FDTC Danesfield/Weston on the Green/Halton</p></td><td><p>1,600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Overseas Eagles</p></td><td><p>600</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>The Ministry of Defence is on target to train these personnel by the end of this financial year. The anticipated average cost per person, based on 5,000 personnel, is around £285.00 per person per week.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-02T16:14:49.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432237/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432237/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Armed Forces: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the aims are of the Eagle training scheme; when that scheme was developed; how many service personnel and reservists from each service have undertaken that scheme; what the cost per trainee of that scheme was; which training centres provided that training; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432238","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<p>Student surveys at Joint School for Adventurous Training Instructors (JSATI) Llanrwst, Force Development Training Centre (FDTC) Crickhowell, Fairbourne and Grantown-on-Spey are conducted at the end of each training course. The information is analysed against training objectives and used for continuous improvement purposes. Students are not requested to provide an overall rating for satisfaction.</p><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-04T14:17:06.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432238/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432238/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what student satisfaction surveys are conducted after training at (a) MOD Grantown-on-Spey, (b) MOD Llanwrst, (c) MOD Fairbourne and (d) MOD Crickhowell; what the average satisfaction rate is; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432239","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<p>The square metres of storage space at each of the four locations are as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Training Centre</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Storage Space (sqm)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Force Development Training Centre (FDTC) Crickhowell</p></td><td><p>302</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>FDTC Fairbourne</p></td><td><p>400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>FDTC Grantown-on-Spey</p></td><td><p>400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>JointSchool for Adventurous Training Instructors (JSATI) Llanwrst</p></td><td><p>502</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Records of when the storage facilities were built are not held. However no storage facilities have been built in the last year. Scoping work for a new storage facility at FDTC Crickhowell is ongoing.</p><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-04T14:09:56.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432239/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432239/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many square meters of stores facilities are available at (a) MOD Grantown-on-Spey, (b) MOD Llanwrst, (c) MOD Fairbourne and (d) MOD Crickhowell; when storage was built in each of those establishments; what the average cost of those storage facilities is; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432240","Ministry of Defence","true","2015-12-02","<p>The military bed space capacity at each of the centres is as follows:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Training Centre</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Bed Spaces</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Force Development Training Centre (FDTC) Crickhowell</p></td><td><p>260</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>FDTC Fairbourne</p></td><td><p>60</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>FDTC Grantown-on-Spey</p></td><td><p>40</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Joint School for Adventurous Training Instructors (JSATI) Llanwrst</p></td><td><p>4<del class="ministerial">2</del><ins class="ministerial">0</ins></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>On occasions, for example when Ministry of Defence accommodation is at full capacity a local bed and breakfast would be used. Records dating back 10 years are not available. However during financial year 2014-15 bed and breakfast accommodation has been utilised as follows:</p><p>FDTC Fairbourne (18 nights’ accommodation) and <ins class="ministerial">as at December 2016 for financial year 2015-16: </ins>FDTC Grantown (64 nights’ accommodation).</p><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-02T16:14:03.477Z","2016-01-28T14:07:05.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432240/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432240/answer","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432240/answer/previousversion/33221","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will detail what accommodation has been available for trainees at (a) MOD Grantown-on-Spey, (b) MOD Llanwrst, (c) MOD Fairbourne and (d) MOD Crickhowell in each of the last 10 years; whether external bed and breakfast accommodation is used for trainees at any of those centres; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432241","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>The RAF constantly reviews its adventurous training to ensure the training being delivered best meets its requirements.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-03T16:30:53.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432241/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432241/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-25","Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of specialist skills and training available for armed forces personnel at (a) MOD Llanwrst and (b) MOD Fairbourne; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","17677"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432242","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-01","<p>Information available on the number of personnel at each of the locations requested is provided in the tables below. The number of military personnel and civil servants is as at 1 October for each year. Data for military personnel can only be provided for the last nine years as prior to this information is not held centrally. The number of contractors can only be provided by financial year.</p><p>The data has been rounded in accordance with data protection principles where ~ denotes less than 5.</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="5"><p><strong>Military Personnel as at 1 October </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>Grantown-on-Spey</p></td><td><p>Llanwrst</p></td><td><p>Fairbourne</p></td><td><p>Crickhowell</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>30</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>30</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>30</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>30</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="5"><p><strong>Civil Servant Personnel as at 1 October</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>Grantown-on-Spey</p></td><td><p>Llanwrst</p></td><td><p>Fairbourne</p></td><td><p>Crickhowell</p