"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432342","Women and Equalities","false","2015-11-30","<p>There are currently two special advisers, one male and one female, who work for the Secretary of State for Education and Minister for Women and Equalities, whose responsibilities include women’s and equalities issues.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-11-30T17:49:14.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432342/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432342/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432342/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2015-11-25","Government Equalities Office: Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, how many people of each gender work as special advisers in the Government Equalities Office.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","17653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432343","Women and Equalities","false","2015-11-30","<p>There are currently 35 female and 20 male members of staff in the Government Equalities Office.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-11-30T17:00:03.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432343/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432343/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432343/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2015-11-25","Government Equalities Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, how many people of each gender work in the Government Equalities Office.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","17654"
